# Task: GitHub Stars Fetching and Caching

## Purpose
Fetch and cache GitHub star counts for all tools to display on the /tldr page.
Stars provide social proof and should be reasonably up-to-date.

## Approach Options

### Option A: Build-Time Fetching (Recommended)
Fetch stars during build, cache in static data:
- No runtime API calls
- Fast page loads
- Stars update on each deploy
- Uses existing lib/github-stats.ts pattern

### Option B: Runtime Fetching with Cache
Fetch client-side with caching:
- Real-time star counts
- API rate limit concerns
- Additional complexity
- Loading states needed

## Implementation (Option A)

### Update build process
```typescript
// scripts/fetch-tool-stars.ts
import { Octokit } from "@octokit/rest";

const octokit = new Octokit({ auth: process.env.GITHUB_TOKEN });

const TOOL_REPOS = [
  { id: 'ntm', repo: 'Dicklesworthstone/ntm' },
  { id: 'slb', repo: 'Dicklesworthstone/simultaneous_launch_button' },
  // ... all 13 tools
];

async function fetchAllStars() {
  const stars: Record<string, number> = {};

  for (const { id, repo } of TOOL_REPOS) {
    const [owner, name] = repo.split('/');
    const { data } = await octokit.repos.get({ owner, repo: name });
    stars[id] = data.stargazers_count;
    console.log(`[STARS] ${id}: ${data.stargazers_count}`);
  }

  return stars;
}

// Write to lib/data/tldr-stars.json
```

### Update tldr-data.ts
```typescript
import starsData from './data/tldr-stars.json';

export const tldrTools: TldrTool[] = [
  {
    id: 'ntm',
    stars: starsData.ntm ?? 0,
    // ...
  }
];
```

### Build script integration
```json
{
  "scripts": {
    "prebuild": "bun run scripts/fetch-tool-stars.ts",
    "build": "next build"
  }
}
```

## Fallback Handling
```typescript
// If stars data is missing or stale, use hardcoded fallbacks
const DEFAULT_STARS: Record<string, number> = {
  'ntm': 69,
  'agent-mail': 1400,
  // ... from content.ts
};

export const getToolStars = (toolId: string): number => {
  return starsData[toolId] ?? DEFAULT_STARS[toolId] ?? 0;
};
```

## Caching Strategy
- Stars cached in JSON file
- Updated on each build
- Fallback to hardcoded values if fetch fails
- No runtime API calls

## Error Handling
```typescript
async function fetchStarsSafely() {
  try {
    return await fetchAllStars();
  } catch (error) {
    console.warn('[STARS] Failed to fetch, using cached values');
    return existingStarsData;
  }
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All 13 tools have star counts
- [ ] Stars update on each deploy
- [ ] Build doesn't fail if GitHub API unavailable
- [ ] Fallback values reasonable

# Task: Implement Nvidia Story Page

## Objective
Create the actual page at /nvidia-story (or chosen URL) that assembles all the components.

## CRITICAL: File Discipline (per AGENTS.md)
- **Data**: All Nvidia story data goes in lib/content.ts - do NOT create lib/nvidia-story-data.ts
- **Components**: Minimize new files. Prefer ONE nvidia-story.tsx file containing all sub-components as internal components, or at most 2 files.
- **Bar for new files is incredibly high** - resist the urge to create many small files

## Recommended File Structure (Minimal)
```
app/nvidia-story/
  page.tsx              # Main page, imports the single component

components/
  nvidia-story.tsx      # ALL Nvidia story UI in one file (internal sub-components)

lib/content.ts          # Add nvidiaStoryData object here
```

